{
  "texts": [
    "Blockchain technology can provide a secure and tamperresistant mechanism for storing and sharing medical data in a decentralized manner.",
    "The use of blockchain can also ensure that data are only accessible by authorized parties, and provide a way to audit data access and usage.",
    "However, there are also challenges associated with the use of blockchain in this context.",
    "For example, there are concerns about the scalability of blockchain systems and the complexity of integrating blockchain with existing systems [143].",
    "Moreover, the use of blockchain in medical applications raises ethical and regulatory considerations related to data ownership and consent."
  ]
}